Veteran Nigerian actress Taiwo Ajai-Lycett, OON, recently left many of her fans in a state of awe after she decided to let down her hair on Sunday, June 19, 2022. The actress was a guest at the 50th birthday ceremony of one of Nigeria’s leading journalists and editor, Olumide Iyanda. Ajai-Lycett, who sat close to art curator and media executive Jahman Anikulapo, couldn’t hide her joy as she danced happily with the host and his wife. Fans of the screen star present at the event also had opportunities to not only take pictures with her but also danced heartily with her.   TG Omori shoots over 405 music videos in five years     Emerging fashion entrepreneurs meet at Fashions Finest…     AFRIMA 2022: Entry submission portal closes on August 5   The Nation reliably gathered that Ajai-Lycett share a long-time friendship with Iyanda since they met in 2000. According to Iyanda, “We have been friends since 2000 when I interviewed her for an article in Tempo magazine. TAL brings the sun everywhere she goes. Even a certified grump like me wears a smile in her presence. The event, which took place in the confines of Iyanda’s home in Ikeja had several media executives and politicians in attendance. On May 14, Ajai-Lycett was awarded the industry merit award at the 2022 edition of the Africa Magic Viewers Choice Awards.